\f0\fs20 \cf0 $E_1^B=qE_1^R+(1-q)E_1^L$. $E_1^i=\\EE[\\max\\\{V_2^i-D,0\\\}]=V_1^i-C_1^i$ where $i\\in\\\{R,L\\\}$. Thus, $E_1^B=V_1^B-C_1^B$. Because $E_1^i\\ge0$ for both $i$, $E_1^B\\ge0$ or equivalently $V_1^B\\ge C_1^B$.}

