\f0\fs20 \cf0 Although altering the financial terms of a debt contract outside bankruptcy requires the unanimous consent of creditors[#UnitedStates1939], if accepted by at least a supra-majority, the firm can file for a pre-pack bankruptcy. Pre-pack bankruptcies fast-track approval (or approve by default) workout agreements supported by a certain majority of creditors in each class.}

