\f0\fs20 \cf0 In jurisdictions without so-called "pre-pack" bankruptcy, any single creditor can instigate formal bankruptcy procedures, meaning out-of-court workouts must be unanimously accepted by creditors. To prevent this type of hold-up, other jurisdictions (including the U.K. and U.S.) fast-track approval (or approve by default) workout agreements supported by a certain majority of creditors in each class.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1502
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Verdana;}
